cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with image retrieval, which is a computer vision task, hence cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a framework for embedding learning, which involves optimization and generalization, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the importance of attention mechanisms, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a novel framework for decoupled metric learning, which could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
